Key Match Events: The Utah Jazz kept it close with the Phoenix Suns but ultimately lost 114-106.
Phoenix led by as much as 16 points during the game.
Utah cut the deficit down to one point in the third quarter.
Lauri Markkanen led the Jazz with 24 points.
Collin Sexton and Walker Kessler scored 20 and 16 points respectively.
Elijah Harkless made his NBA debut.
Will Hardy challenged an out-of-bounds call against the Jazz, which was unsuccessful and resulted in two free throws for Beal.
Pre-Game Insights: The Utah Jazz were missing several key players due to injuries, including Johnny Juzang, Brice Sensabaugh, Jordan Clarkson, John Collins, and Keyonte George.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cody Williams had a career night, showing significant improvement in his performance.
The Jazz will return to Delta Center for a two-game homestand to host the Nets and the Hornets.
